data.content:
noun
plural ~ -es
[count] a person (such as a politician), animal, or thing that competes in a race or other contest and is not expected to win
The Democrat from Utah has gone from being a dark horse to the front-runner in the campaign for President.
The movie is a dark horse for the award.
Brit :a person who has interesting qualities or abilities that most people do not know about
He is a dark horse, but I did find out that he once played football professionally.

người kín miệng
he's a bit of a dark horse, he was earning a fortune, but nobody knew
anh ta là một tay kín miệng, anh ta kiếm ra bộn tiền mà không ai biết cả
